name: fluff magazine got issues 20
description: fluff is possibly the world's most unique skateboard magazine, filled with "wildlife photos of skateboarders an their friends in their natural habitat". published in the netherlands since 2000, this special 20th issue is actually 8 glue bound zines, titled "fluff got issues", with skate and non-skate photos of youness amrani, justin brock, nassim guammaz, dan plunkett, tom remillard, wieger van wageningen, , tim zom, and a slew of others. - released sept 2013 up to 7" x 8 3/4" glue bound full color - also awesome about fluff is the lack of explanation available online, you just have to see it. www.fluff.me/ www.facebook.com/fluffmagazine/ - due to the weight of this item, postage gets pricey, so we've slightly lowered the price from $15 suggested retail. it will not ship with prints.

name: grey skate mag volume 02 issue 02
description:
grey is a london based independent skateboard magazine, and one of our favorites. there's always amazing photography by publisher henry kingsford, lex kembery and more. it's well printed put together in a very nice, small format.

grey is free if you can find it, but it's only in about 10 skate shops in the US. if you can't get to one, or it runs out before you get there, we've ordered some so you can have it mailed to you.

-

full color
